[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man killed confronting moped thieves outside his home

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been stabbed to death while trying to stop a group of people from stealing a moped outside his home.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 27-year-old was with his father when he confronted the four men in Chadwell Heath, east London, at 01:35 BST on Tuesday.
Both suffered knife wounds in the attack on Gibbfield Close and the son later died in hospital.
Detectives said two males had been arrested on Wednesday morning on suspicion of murder.
The victim's 46-year-old father remains in hospital, although his injuries are not thought to be life-threatening.
